## Public-Private Partnerships

[Helion announced](https://www.helionenergy.com/articles/helion-achieves-new-fusion-energy-milestones/) its Polaris prototype achieved measurable deuterium‑tritium (D‑T) fusion and reached plasma temperatures of 150 million °C.

[Inertia announced](https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2026/02/11/3236274/0/en/Inertia-raises-450-million-to-commercialize-the-only-proven-fusion-science.html) a $450 million Series A financing to commercialize laser-based inertial fusion.

[Pacific Fusion reported](https://www.pacificfusion.com/updates/experimental-breakthrough-by-pacific-fusion-clears-major-obstacle-to-affordable-commercial-fusion) results from four experiments at Sandia National Laboratories’ Z Pulsed Power Facility measuring magnetic-field diffusion in simplified aluminum-and-plastic targets, aiming to eliminate external magnetic coils for pre‑magnetization.

[The New Zealand government announced](https://www.beehive.govt.nz/release/government-backs-fusion-energy-research) it will invest up to NZ$35 million (as a loan via the Regional Infrastructure Fund) to support a specialized facility for OpenStar’s next fusion machine. 

[Helical Fusion announced](https://www.einpresswire.com/article/889310123/helical-fusion-completes-coil-manufacturing-machine-for-its-integrated-demo-device-in-collaboration-with-sugino-machine) it completed a coil manufacturing machine, developed with Sugino Machine Limited, intended to produce high‑temperature superconducting (HTS) coils for its integrated demonstration device “Helix HARUKA.”

[Xcimer published](https://xcimer.energy/stimulated-brillouin-scattering/) an update stating new SBS (Stimulated Brillouin Scattering) measurements in low-pressure noble gases support its pulse-compression architecture for laser fusion, and referenced ongoing work on its “Phoenix” prototype system. 

Renewal Fuels (operating as “American Fusion”) announced the [appointment of Dr. John E. Brandenburg as Chief Technology Officer](https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2026/02/06/3234046/0/en/Renewal-Fuels-Inc-OTC-RNWF-Operating-as-American-Fusion-Appoints-Dr-John-E-Brandenburg-Ph-D-as-Chief-Technology-Officer.html) and [Dwight Cartwright as Chief Operating Officer](https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2026/02/12/3237157/0/en/Renewal-Fuels-Inc-OTC-RNWF-Operating-as-American-Fusion-Appoints-Dwight-Cartwright-as-Chief-Operating-Officer.html) and as a member of the Board of Directors. 

[U.S. Department of Energy announced](https://www.energy.gov/articles/energy-department-announces-members-office-science-advisory-committee-strengthening-gold?utm_source=chatgpt.com) the inaugural membership of a new DOE Office of Science Advisory Committee (SCAC), a cross-cutting body that will advise on major Office of Science initiatives including fusion; this is an early signal of which scientific/industrial priorities may get elevated in DOE’s science agenda.

[Gavin Newsom’s office highlighted fusion](https://www.gov.ca.gov/2026/02/03/governor-newsoms-statewide-jobs-first-investments-created-more-than-61000-jobs-trained-more-than-142000-workers-in-2025/) as a state “bet sector” (alongside quantum) in a statewide economic development update.

[Fusion for Energy reported](https://fusionforenergy.europa.eu/news/cask-transport-system-final-acceptance-tests/) successful acceptance tests of an ITER cask transport system.

[Fusion for Energy and Gauss Fusion signed a collaboration agreement](https://fusionforenergy.europa.eu/news/f4e-and-gauss-fusion-sign-collaboration-agreement/) focused on knowledge exchange for magnets, advanced materials, and tritium breeding blankets.

[Ministry of Science and ICT (via National Research Foundation of Korea) posted a new competitive call](https://www.ntis.go.kr/rndgate/eg/un/ra/view.do?flag=rndList&roRndUid=1256578) for an “AI-based digital virtual fusion reactor platform” R&D effort.

[MSIT/NRF also posted a new call for the “nuclear fusion plug-in program,”](https://www.ntis.go.kr/rndgate/eg/un/ra/view.do?roRndUid=1256591) positioned as an “innovative fusion” challenge-technology development line.

[General Fusion appointed Wendy Kei as a Strategic Advisor](https://generalfusion.com/post/wendy-kei-strategic-advisor/).

[Spring Valley’s Form 425](https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/2074850/000110465926009888/tm265042d1_425.htm) (re: General Fusion) adds fresh, SEC-filed transaction communications and confirms the parties anticipate a registration statement/proxy process (Form F‑4 referenced). 

[InvestorBrandNetwork (IBN) announced](https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2026/02/11/3236280/0/en/IBN-Initiates-Coverage-of-Renewal-Fuels-Inc-Operating-as-American-Fusion.html) (via press release) that RNWF/American Fusion engaged it for corporate communications strategy.

[ENEA reported acceptance testing of a 170 GHz, 1 MW gyrotron](https://www.media.enea.it/en/press-releases-and-news/years-archive/year-2026/nuclear-fusion-energy-divertor-tokamak-test-reaches-a-major-milestone.html) for Italy’s DTT program: 1 MW at 170 GHz for 100 seconds and 95% reliability (19/20 pulses), with follow-on manufacture of additional units under contract. 

[Financial Times cited PitchBook that fusion startups completed 43 funding rounds raising $2.3B in 2025](https://www.ft.com/content/ff24f3af-3b7a-4469-bd8b-9eb183d7c415) (record deal count; largest total since 2021) and argued the sector is turning toward public markets because projects now run into the billions. 

[Comments on the Paper “Fundamental Scaling of Adiabatic Compression of Field Reversed Configuration Thermonuclear Fusion Plasmas”](https://link.springer.com/article/10.1007/s10894-026-00554-2)

[Fujikura announced ¥5.6 billion in additional capital investment](https://www.fujikura.co.jp/en/news/pressrelease/20260209post_110.html) for production expansion facilities for high-temperature superconductors (HTS), citing expected demand growth tied to fusion energy development.

In an Microsoft Azure blog post, p=[Microsoft said it is investigating high-temperature superconductors](https://azure.microsoft.com/en-us/blog/can-high-temperature-superconductors-transform-the-power-infrastructure-of-datacenters/) (HTS) for datacenter power infrastructure and describes HTS as relying on “scalable high-availability cooling systems” to maintain cryogenic temperatures.









